1
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,720
Why do we get to have fun out here today?

2
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:17,280
Who said we’re here for fun?

3
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:20,279
Comrade Ploeng trusted you to reach the villagers.

4
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:21,879
We’re here to work.

5
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:24,239
Yeah, I know. I'm just messing with you.

6
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:26,336
Our job is to get as many villagers on our side as possible.

7
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,600
The more people trust us, the faster we win.

8
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:31,640
If you want to gain people's trust,

9
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,480
you must know how to give first.

10
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:36,600
If you just walk in like that, why would anyone follow you?

11
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:37,840
Give?

12
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:41,520
We barely even have meat to eat. What can we give?

13
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:48,879
Give what you can. Eat just enough. Use just enough.

14
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,279
Share whatever’s left with others.

15
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,519
If there is nothing to give, you give them a hand.

16
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:55,480
It’s that simple. Students like you should understand that.

17
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,520
Hey! Help!

18
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,399
Help!

19
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,400
Help! Please help my son!

20
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,840
Help! Please help my son!

21
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:09,320
Please help, my son is dying!

22
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:12,120
Lead the way, sir.

23
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,440
This way.

24
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,199
Aaaah! (crying)

25
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,200
Yaguar!

26
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:22,439
We can only clean the wound and apply herbs.

27
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:22,800
Yes.

28
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:25,199
What happened to his son?

29
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,920
An explosion.

30
00:01:25,921 --> 00:01:27,039
What? An explosion?!

31
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,519
He stepped on it while gathering bamboo shoots

32
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,639
in the forest yesterday.

33
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:30,640
Yesterday?

34
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,679
Then why didn’t you take him to a hospital?

35
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,119
Or a clinic in town?

36
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,559
He’d die on the way before we even get there.

37
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,719
They don’t have money. No ID cards.

38
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,080
No one cares about them.

39
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:42,640
We’ll do what we can with the medicine we have.

40
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,520
Aaah…! (in pain)

41
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:53,560
Aaah…!

42
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,240
Are you scared!

43
00:02:01,241 --> 00:02:02,879
Aaah…! (in pain)

44
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:05,040
Aaah…!

45
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,080
I know this place is far.

46
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:12,760
But if they want to see a doctor, they should be able to.

47
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,759
When I went on volunteer camps,

48
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,360
I saw inequality everywhere.

49
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,280
But this place is on another level.

50
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:32,840
Are you listening?

51
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,080
I used to be like you.

52
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:48,680
But getting angry doesn’t fix anything.

53
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:55,600
Better to use that anger to help people.

54
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:00,760
And don’t let your it follow you into your dreams.

55
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,240
Do I really look that weak?

56
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,680
And just now…

57
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,360
Who was the one hiding behind me?

58
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,840
Being scared isn’t something to be ashamed of.

59
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:21,480
I wasn't scared. Just a little startled.

60
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,640
Aaaah!!!

61
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,640
Aaaah!!!

62
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:31,000
Aaaah!!!

63
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,079
Uncle, please go tell all other fellow villagers

64
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:21,840
that the comrades in the forest are ready to help everyone.

65
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,759
No matter what happens,

66
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,920
we’ll always stand by the people.

67
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,640
Okay.

68
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:31,039
Here, this is pain killer.

69
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,039
Take two pills when it hurts.

70
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,200
I’m giving you eight tablets.

71
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,680
Thank you so much.

72
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,959
Well, I’ll go check on my mom now.

73
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:48,599
Comrade Roong… do you have any medicine left?

74
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:51,120
Don’t worry, I prepared some already.

75
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,639
But I can’t go with you today.

76
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,639
I have to return to base. Some unfinished business.

77
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:56,640
That’s totally fine.

78
00:04:56,641 --> 00:04:58,720
You’ve been of great help already. Thank you.

79
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,199
I want to visit Yaguar’s mother.

80
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,359
Let’s go together.

81
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,360
Comrade Roong!

82
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,680
You’re heading back, right? I’ll go with you.

83
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,800
I need to finish my article.

84
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,160
Alright.

85
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:29,200
Comrade Roong sent some fever and cough medicine for you, mom.

86
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,199
But she's busy so she couldn’t come herself.

87
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:35,119
And this is Comrade Ying and Comrade Saeng

88
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,960
the ones I told you about.

89
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:36,999
Hello, ma'am.

90
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,599
Thank you, dear. Bless you.

91
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,600
Thank you, ma’am.

92
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,519
How are you feeling?

93
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:48,520
Fever and coughing on and off for about a month now.

94
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:52,920
Chronic symptoms like this need a proper check-up.

95
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:56,679
Comrade Roong thinks it might be tuberculosis.

96
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,639
It needs continuous treatment.

97
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:01,559
And we don’t have medicine for that at the base.

98
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,720
I’m saving money, though.

99
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,920
Thank you.

100
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,600
Eat first, mom.

101
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,400
Here, let me help you.

102
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:16,439
Back when I was a student.

103
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:18,760
Some seniors volunteered with doctors up in the mountains.

104
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,319
Do you have that here, Yaguar?

105
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:23,759
Used to. about two years ago.

106
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,960
Two years ago?

107
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:38,239
Then what do the villagers do without doctors?

108
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:41,560
They go into the forest to gather herbs to make medicine.

109
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,880
Anyone home?

110
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,960
Anyone here?

111
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,360
Yaguar.

112
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,840
Is your mother feeling better?

113
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,559
You already saved my mother.

114
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,239
I owe you more than I can repay.

115
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,680
And now you’re bringing more things.

116
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,159
I can’t accept this.

117
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:41,920
Just take it. It’s only some fruit. Nothing much at all.

118
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,840
Besides, the reason I came here

119
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,136
is to talk to the village head about the farmland.

120
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,000
Farmland?
Yup.

121
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:51,479
I’m planning to buy the field at the end of the village.

122
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,239
But it's my rice field there now.

123
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,640
Yaguar, I’m not kicking you out.

124
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,840
It’s just a change of ownership. Everything stays the same.

125
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,160
In fact… it might even be better.

126
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,039
If I lose that land… I don’t know how I’ll survive anymore.

127
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,519
I’ll never forget this kindness.

128
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:11,679
Thank you so much.

129
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,719
Anything I can do for you at all, please tell me.

130
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,720
Yaguar,

131
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,560
I’m not going to make you do anything.

132
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,680
I just need a little hand is all.

133
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,200
Why are you sneaking off for a nap here?

134
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,199
It's only just the first day visiting the villagers

135
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,639
and you’re already dozing off?

136
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,560
How would you even be able to go to battle then?

137
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,760
I wasn’t sleeping.

138
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:48,800
I was just resting my eyes.

139
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,560
Besides, I’d fight my ass off if I had to.

140
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,999
If you don’t want to be in the combat unit, just say it.

141
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,079
No pressure.

142
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,679
I’m willing to.

143
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,280
The more people we have carrying guns,

144
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,160
the sooner we all get to go home.

145
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,239
Maybe it’s in my blood.

146
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,280
I keep putting myself in dangerous situations.

147
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,920
No one shares their private lives here.

148
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,360
If you don’t want to hear it, then don’t.

149
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,360
You want to be like your father?

150
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,720
I don’t want to be like him.

151
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,440
My father passed away a long time ago.

152
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,760
Mine too.

153
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,160
With a skilled comrade like you,

154
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,040
I’m not dying that easy.

155
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,639
Now that you're with me.

156
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,039
If soldiers come, I’ll just hide behind a soldier.

157
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:58,080
I mean, behind you. I’ll survive just fine.

158
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,120
You better avoid the front lines then.

159
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,960
I don’t feel like taking care of you.

160
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:08,319
How can you put me in the back?

161
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:11,600
For someone this good like me.

162
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,800
That'd be a waste.

163
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,520
Comrade Gaun Hin.

164
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:37,200
So here you are. I’ve been looking everywhere for you.

165
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,440
Thought you were sick. You didn’t show up for food.

166
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,760
The work’s not finished yet.

167
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,560
I’ll come once I’m done.

168
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,640
It’s already too late now. 67.

169
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:53,080
You know we have to eat on time here.

170
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,159
It's just that yesterday visit to the villagers,

171
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,400
It gave me tons to write about.

172
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,359
Wait till you read it, Comrade Saeng.

173
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:05,560
This issue’s going to be a hit.

174
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,160
Hey, Sila.

175
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:10,360
Lemme ask you something.

176
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,480
Do you still see Mada as your girlfriend?

177
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:18,679
You’re so distant. Like you don’t even know each other.

178
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:21,280
Did you forget Comrade Ploeng’s Three Delays Policy?

179
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,959
We came to the forest to serve collectively.

180
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,639
Ideology comes first. Love comes later.

181
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:28,640
Don’t you remember?

182
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,479
Go tell Mada then.

183
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,839
That you chose ideology over love.

184
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,799
But you need to know your place, don’t you?

185
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,439
You don’t have to say everything out loud.

186
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,880
Acting childish like this.

187
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,200
How are you going to achieve anything big?

188
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:45,600
Besides, in here you’re Comrade Saeng.

189
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,719
I’m Comrade Gaun Hin.

190
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,440
Please use the right names.

191
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,600
What’s up with you?

192
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:56,159
So to do something big, we have to forget who we are?

193
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,279
Forget what we’ve felt?

194
00:12:57,280 --> 00:13:00,159
Love and ideology can go together, you know.

195
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,736
Time to go to the training now, shall we?

196
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:03,440
Comrade Yue’s been waiting forever by now.

197
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,679
I'll leave you alone here then.

198
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,680
Suit yourself.

199
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:42,040
Easy… hold it steady.

200
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,040
Lower the barrel a bit.

201
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:52,240
Now take a deep breath. And slowly exhale.

202
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,320
Hold it.

203
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,240
When was the last time you washed your hair?

204
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,080
You made me run so many rounds this morning.

205
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,719
Of course I smell like sweat.

206
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:31,720
Then step back.

207
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,720
If something’s bothering you, say it.

208
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,480
Otherwise, you won’t hit your target today.

209
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,560
Sila—uh, I mean Comrade Gaun Hin…

210
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,696
He’s been acting really different lately.

211
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,320
Like I’m not even his friend anymore.

212
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,160
And so is Comrade Ying. She’s acting strange.

213
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,680
Cause you guys don't talk things through.

214
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:13,640
Your friends might just be focused on their goals.

215
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,720
Setting everything else aside.

216
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,720
Just like when you’re aiming forward,

217
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:30,040
you don’t see what’s around you.

218
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,880
But you don't have to push people away.

219
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,319
You don’t aim your gun all the time.

220
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,320
Or do you?

221
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,520
You need breaks too.

222
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:45,599
If this keeps going,

223
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,200
those two might actually break up.

224
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:51,600
All you can do is look out from a distance.

225
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,239
It's okay to be worried.

226
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:57,880
But not so worried that it messes you up.

227
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,080
Go to sleep.

228
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,320
Take a seat.

229
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,920
We successfully took Baan Prongdong.

230
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,800
Next mission: Baan Saeng Dao.

231
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,040
Last stop before the northern headquarter.

232
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,840
I have an informant inside Baan Saeng Dao.

233
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,639
Taking that base shouldn’t be difficult.

234
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:47,960
Yang Sue only gets surface-level intel.

235
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,080
Nothing from the inside.

236
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,600
I have someone that could breach in..

237
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,800
But I need a bit more time to win his trust.

238
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,520
What an effort,

239
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:01,640
General Khong Khai must be proud of his son.

240
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,320
Yes, sir.

241
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:10,600
Given that, may I be assigned to Baan Prongdong?

242
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:13,239
My informant is in that area.

243
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,560
It’ll be easier to coordinate.

244
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,639
Don’t mess this up, Dan Din.

245
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:21,480
I’m counting on you for this mission.

246
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,240
Understood, sir.

247
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:57,480
Yes! I did it! I did it! I did it!!

248
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,280
Woohoo!

249
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:02,520
I did it. I actually did it!

250
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:04,880
Nice one, Comrade Saeng.

251
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,440
Good teacher makes a fast learner.

252
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,119
Hey what are you doing? I’m not dead yet.

253
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,640
Thought you were holding your breath with me.

254
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:35,040
Keep training. One hit and you start bragging?

255
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,680
Will do, sirrr.

256
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:03,720
Focus. This isn’t a toy.

257
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:06,399
I can’t chop firewood.

258
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,200
I’m better at using my brain.

259
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,400
Whether it’s strength or brains, it’s the same.

260
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:15,080
With that attitude, you shouldn’t be writing anything at all.

261
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,760
Keep chopping until you can do it.

262
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,320
Even if I chop all day and night, I'm getting nowhere.

263
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,120
Comrade Fah.

264
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:29,280
If Comrade Gaun Hin can’t do it, show him how.

265
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:39,360
Comrade Ploeng. Comrade Ploeng. Comrade.

266
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,880
What is it?

267
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:45,080
We got news from headquarter.

268
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:57,520
What's wrong, dad?

269
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,560
I'm fine, dear.

270
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:09,039
The headquarter ordered us to retake Baan Prongdong

271
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,520
from the soldiers.

272
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:13,159
Even Baan Prongdong, which was better prepared than us,

273
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,520
Still surrendered to the soldiers.

274
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,760
So why are we being sent into risk?

275
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,719
Though we're only a few of us,

276
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,720
our combat units are all highly skilled.

277
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:25,240
We minimize direct clashes. Keep it tight.

278
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,919
Comrade Yue, prepare the snipers.

279
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,440
We’ll ambush.

280
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,679
May I request more man power?

281
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,720
More man power?

282
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,840
From which unit?

283
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:52,800
If you have someone in mind, say it.

284
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,120
Going to bathe?

285
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:18,680
The water’s nice and cold. I'm fresh out of the water.

286
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,040
Vin!

287
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,440
What is it, Comrade Gaun Hin?

288
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,440
Are you ready?

289
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,679
I am as I am and always have been.

290
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:52,880
And you…already know me well.

291
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,480
If it’s too much.

292
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:01,520
I’ll try to do better then.

293
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:24,760
Get ready. Tomorrow, you'll be stuck with me.

294
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,920
Wait, what?

295
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:32,680
I mean to the battle.

296
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,880
Not bathing?

297
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,799
Boiled water. Carry it with you.

298
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,400
To keep hydrated on the way.

299
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,120
Cold?

300
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:21,160
I chilled it by the stream. Nice and refreshing.

301
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,880
Come back safe, Comrade Yue.

302
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,599
Good luck, bro.

303
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:41,360
You’re the first in our batch to go into battle.

304
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:43,520
Thanks.

305
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:49,760
You don’t have to win. Just come back safe.

306
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:51,240
Piece of cake.

307
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:54,039
As if I'm just going to shooting range.

308
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,320
I’ll be back in no time.

309
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,000
You’ve got this, Comrade Saeng.

310
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,960
Come on, let’s go see the others.

311
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,960
Have some water. It’ll refresh you.

312
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:20,200
Nice and cold.

313
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:31,880
So refreshing.

314
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:40,079
Now our Baan Prongdong has been crushed by the soldiers.

315
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:42,159
Their bullets. Their bombs.

316
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:44,359
We will reclaim our honor.

317
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:46,320
We will take back Baan Prongdong.

318
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:48,879
Not just as a base—.

319
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:51,599
But as the heart of the people.

320
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:54,879
All units heading into battle today—.

321
00:25:54,880 --> 00:26:00,639
Follow Comrade Yue’s orders. And remember.

322
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:04,199
That victory is waiting for us ahead.

323
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,959
Hey!!!

324
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:09,120
Sniper, take your position here. Find your right spot.

325
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,279
Take down as many soldiers as possible.

326
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:12,640
Minimize direct engagement.

327
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,280
Can we not kill?

328
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,160
This is war, not a trip.

329
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:22,680
Get to your position.

330
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,200
If you don’t want to kill

331
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:35,919
just make sure they can’t pick up a gun again.

332
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:37,399
Follow my orders.

333
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:41,360
No matter what happens, do not leave your cover.

334
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,360
Not until it’s over.

335
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,800
Do you want to retreat?

336
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:00,920
I’m scared. But I won’t run.

337
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:06,920
We’ll win together. Trust me.

338
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:21,320
Sergeant.

339
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:22,560
Yes, sir.

340
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:26,280
Status? See anything fishy?

341
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,720
All clear.

342
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:32,800
Sir, any word from the northern unit?

343
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:38,520
Just in. They can’t send supply unit for the next two days.

344
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:39,960
Damn.

345
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:43,840
If they attack now, we’re almost out of ammo.

346
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:49,160
I’ll handle that myself. Don’t worry.

347
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,640
Aaah!!

348
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,240
Comrade Saeng!

349
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:51,880
Coordinates 34. we’re under attack. Requesting retreat.

350
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:55,600
Fall back!!

351
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,240
Comrade Saeng.

352
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:05,759
Blood blood! Comrade Yue, are you okay?!

353
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:07,599
I’m fine. That’s not my blood.

354
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,600
Comrade Saeng.

355
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,320
I killed a person.

356
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:16,039
You saved my life, Comrade Saeng.

357
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,040
I killed a person.

358
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:21,520
It’s over… it’s all over now, Comrade Saeng.

359
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,160
I killed a person.

360
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:29,200
This isn't how I wanted it. This isn't how I wanted it to be.

361
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,200
It’s over, Comrade Saeng…

362
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,560
The combat unit is back!

363
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:49,160
Everyone listen!

364
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,359
Victory's ours.

365
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,280
Yeah!!

366
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,440
Great job, everyone!
Comrade Ploeng.

367
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,959
Comrade Saeng shot the enemy commander

368
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:00,680
right in the forehead.

369
00:31:00,681 --> 00:31:02,000
One shot. Down instantly.

370
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,640
Right in the forehead?

371
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:08,119
- Comrade Saeng is incredible.
- Ow—.

372
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:11,479
Comrade Baitong, easy. He just got shot.

373
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:14,400
Comrade Roong, come check on him please.

374
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,640
I’m fine. It just grazed me.

375
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:18,920
No, you still need treatment.

376
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,439
Comrade Roong, go prepare the supplies.

377
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,680
I’ll take him to the infirmary.

378
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:24,520
Yes.

379
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,120
Do I really have to…?

380
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,320
Is it going to hurt?

381
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,480
I knew I wasn’t wrong about this kid.

382
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,400
His first time in battle.

383
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,320
It’s not that bad.

384
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:47,599
Treat the others outside first.

385
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:48,760
- I'll be right after.
- Okay.

386
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,960
Ah—!

387
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,440
Ouchhh!!

388
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,400
Don’t you ever do that again.

389
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:02,280
In the battle field, you follow orders.

390
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,000
Understand?

391
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:12,320
But I was worried about you.

392
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:17,479
From this heart that still holds onto your love.

393
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:21,439
Onto the promises.

394
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,639
That no matter how long it takes,

395
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:28,080
no one could ever take your place…

396
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:43,560
I just want to wake up without tears.

397
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:47,559
Wishing it would all fade away.

398
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:52,159
Begging the wind to carry it off.

399
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:56,079
I don’t want to live like this.

400
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:58,560
As someone who never forgets.

401
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:04,319
I could barely breathe.

402
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:08,200
If I knew I’d lose you…

403
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,680
The first time I killed someone,

404
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:14,560
my hands shook just like yours.

405
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:19,000
That moment, I couldn’t even move.

406
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,760
Weren’t you scared?

407
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:26,040
Of course I was.

408
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,360
But I had to do it.

409
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:33,040
Was there... no other choice?

410
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:38,680
Want to stay at my place?

411
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:42,160
You won’t get any sleep in the shared quarter.

412
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,800
People coming and going all day.

413
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:52,440
It's deputy leader's place. Am I allowed?

414
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,400
Why aren't you?

415
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,800
News for the People
NORTHERN LIGHT.

416
00:35:58,480 --> 00:36:01,720
The hands of students ignite the people to rise…

417
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:09,960
Another nightmare?

418
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:31,640
I dreamed of soldiers and explosions.

419
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,240
People dying right in front of me.

420
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:40,480
Blood everywhere.

421
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:44,120
It was terrifying.

422
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:49,960
Why does this water taste strange?

423
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:54,640
Homemade saline. It helps refresh you.

424
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:09,320
Where are you going?

425
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:12,560
I want you to get some rest.

426
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:15,840
You’ve been helping me the whole time…

427
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:18,239
I feel bad.

428
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:21,440
You sleep. I'm way tougher than you.

429
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:25,160
Going a few days without sleep is a breeze.

430
00:38:26,240 --> 00:38:29,479
Then let’s take turns. I’ll share the bed.

431
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,240
I don’t want to take advantage of you.

432
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:34,360
It’s fine. Just sleep.

433
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:43,839
Comrade Saeng,

434
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:47,359
a student who's just recently joined the combat unit

435
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:49,839
exceeded expectations in his first mission.

436
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:52,239
One Shot, One Kill: Enemy Commander Down.

437
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:55,319
How's that? Exciting enough for a headline?

438
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:58,680
Using someone’s death for news… You sure about that?

439
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:02,439
But your achievement boosts everyone’s morale.

440
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,440
Why are you upset?

441
00:40:03,441 --> 00:40:05,399
No matter who dies in the battle field,

442
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:07,079
it’s all terrible.

443
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:09,920
If we won today, but I died there,

444
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:12,559
would you still write a headline like that?

445
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:15,520
Comrade Saeng!! This is about morale,

446
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:17,360
not for fun.

447
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:21,039
We still shouldn’t treat death like this.

448
00:40:21,040 --> 00:40:22,480
Like we’re proud of killing someone.

449
00:40:23,680 --> 00:40:25,760
Hey. Comrade Saeng’s not fully recovered yet.

450
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:27,840
You should leave.

451
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:50,600
I don’t like the way Comrade Gaun Hin writes this.

452
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,280
If their family saw it,

453
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:56,680
how heartbroken would they feel?

454
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:04,320
You took out their commander.

455
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:09,440
You dealed with it before the battle gets out of hand.

456
00:41:11,640 --> 00:41:13,760
We need the people to know that.

457
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:16,920
Comrade Gaun Hin is just doing his job.

458
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:23,879
In war, no one wants a death to be meaningless.

459
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:26,439
If we don’t turn it into strength,

460
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:28,240
how do the living move forward?

461
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,720
If you could turn back time,

462
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:38,480
would you still kill him?

463
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:48,000
I’d do the same.

464
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:53,600
I didn’t want you to die.

465
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:24,000
Maybe I should go sleep in the hut tonight.

466
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:28,200
I don’t want to trouble you.

467
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:33,440
Stay here.

468
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,960
I’ll... take care of you.

469
00:43:58,840 --> 00:44:06,840
I just want to wake up without tears…

470
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:10,839
Wish it would all fade away.

471
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:15,359
Begging the wind to blow it away.

472
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:18,440
I don’t want to live like this.

473
00:44:19,160 --> 00:44:23,519
As someone who never forgets…

474
00:44:23,520 --> 00:44:25,039
I could barely breathe.

475
00:44:25,040 --> 00:44:27,159
- I could barely breathe.
- You treat me so well.

476
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,719
If I knew I’d lose you…

477
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,936
- If I knew I’d lose you…
- It makes it harder for me.

478
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:39,960
I just want to wake up without tears…

479
00:44:40,280 --> 00:44:44,079
Wishing it would all fade away.

480
00:44:44,080 --> 00:44:48,559
Begging the wind to carry it off.

481
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:51,640
I don’t want to live like this.

482
00:44:52,320 --> 00:44:56,799
As someone who never forgets…

483
00:44:56,800 --> 00:45:00,799
I could barely breathe.

484
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:04,880
If I knew I’d lose you…

485
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:13,399
Every night, pretending I can handle it.

486
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:17,599
Not knowing how deep I'm sinking.

487
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:21,399
I’d be fine.

488
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:25,879
I told myself I could live without you…

489
00:45:25,880 --> 00:45:30,319
A world without you might feel lighter.

490
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:36,200
But today, I realize… you've never left
